021 Asian Olympic qualifiers in Pattaya, where she missed out after finishing second and just 0.938 of a second behind Kazakhstan's Natalya Sergeyeva in the K1 500m.\", \"from\": 2282, \"to\": 2511, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2349, \"end\": 2373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Asian_Boxing_Olympic_Qualification_Tournament\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Asian Olympic qualifiers\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Asian_Boxing_Olympic_Qualification_Tournament\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Asian_Boxing_Olympic_Qualification_Tournament\"}, {\"begin\": 2377, \"end\": 2384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pattaya\", \"score\": 0.9999968569813343, \"rank\": 3.14302644519166e-06, \"text\": \"Pattaya\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pattaya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pattaya\"}, {\"begin\": 2465, \"end\": 2475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\", \"score\": 0.9999942392998893, \"rank\": 5.759443526977104e-06, \"text\": \"Kazakhstan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"steady progress\", \"from\": 2318, \"to\": 2333}, {\"ngram\": \"the K1 500m.\", \"from\": 2498, \"to\": 2510}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She went even more agonisingly close a day later in the K1 200m, with a mere 0.067sec standing between her and a ticket to the Tokyo Olympics.\", \"from\": 2513, \"to\": 2655, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the K1\", \"from\": 2565, \"to\": 2571}, {\"ngram\": \"200m\", \"from\": 2572, \"to\": 2576}, {\"ngram\": \"a mere 0.067sec\", \"from\": 2583, \"to\": 2598}, {\"ngram\": \"a ticket\", \"from\": 2624, \"to\": 2632}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 2636, \"to\": 2654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was third in 40.325sec, behind Kazakhstan's Inna Klino